    "plan_content": "Here's the complete implementation plan for `Bun.INI`.\n\n## Summary\n\nThe INI parser already exists in `src/ini.zig` (used internally for `.npmrc` parsing). The work is purely about wiring it up through the same 6-layer pipeline every other format namespace uses.\n\n### Files to **create** (1 file)\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig` | New API wrapper with `create()`, `parse()`, `stringify()` |\n\n### Files to **modify** (6 files)\n\n| File | Change |\n|---|---|\n| `src/bun.js/api.zig` | Add `pub const INIObject = @import(\"./api/INIObject.zig\");` |\n| `src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig` | Add lazy property `INI`, getter `getINIObject()`, and import |\n| `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h` | Add `macro(INI)` to `FOR_EACH_GETTER` |\n| `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp` | Add `INI BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI DontDelete|PropertyCallback` to the hash table |\n| `packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts` | Add `namespace INI { parse, stringify }` |\n| `test/js/bun/ini/ini.test.ts` | Add `describe(\"Bun.INI public API\")` tests |\n\n### Key implementation notes\n\n- **`parse`**: Directly reuses `ini.Parser` from `src/ini.zig`. Needs `globalThis.bunVM().transpiler.env` for `${VAR}` substitution (same as the internal testing API). Calls `parser.out.toJS()` for the result.\n- **`stringify`**: Written from scratch in `INIObject.zig`. Two-pass: top-level primitives → `key = value`, nested objects → `[section]` blocks with dot-notation for deep nesting. Uses `jsc.JSPropertyIterator` + `wtf.StringBuilder`.\n- The `toJSLazyPropertyCallback` helper auto-generates and exports the `BunObject_lazyPropCb_INI` C symbol — no manual `@export` needed.",
